caption.p: MAYV infection is associated with acute production of inflammatory mediators. 6-week-old BALB/c mice were inoculated or not with wt MAYV (2 × 10 5 PFU/50 μL, i.pl.) and levels of ( a) IL1-β; ( b) IL-6; ( c) IFN-γ; ( d) TNF-α; ( e) VEGF; ( f) IL-17; ( g) IL-10; ( h) CXCL-1; ( i) CCL2; ( j) CCL3; ( k) CCL4 and ( l) CCL5 in the spleen were analyzed by ELISA in different time-points. Results are expressed as pg/100 mg of spleen. Data is representative of two experiments expressed as mean ± SEM. *p < 0.05 when compared to control uninfected mice (MOCK), as assessed by one-way ANOVA followed by Newman-Keuls post-test.
